race.comment: Tricky race to kick off the card with many of these babies facing the starter for the first time. BOOTS (2) is one of them but has shown plenty of ability winning a recent trial here by over six lengths and hoop Bayliss stays on top for race day. Dam was a dual-Listed winner and a strong showing on debut would not surprise. I AM THAT GIRL (12) was well in the betting first time at the races but just missed the placings on that occasion. Where there's smoke there's fire and gets the reliable Gollan/Jones combination. Capable of sharp improvement. SCARTOON (7) just ran into one better at Eagle Farm on debut and will have derived a stack of benefit from that race day experience. Top-three candidate. ELUSIVE CAPITAL (9) is sure to be well-educated from the Freedman barn and a watch on betting is advised. TRAMCA (6) best of the rest.
